const summaries = { lastRace: "Nora topped JPN with 47 points — nearly 25 above the league average — powered by Oscar Piastri's 43-point bounce-back after two straight DNFs. At the other end, Mary Beth (2) and David (3) were basically no-shows, with Lance Stroll and Alexander Albon doing their worst again. Kimi Antonelli's 50-point masterclass kept Timo firmly in front despite Bearman's DNF clawing back 14 points.", season: "Timo leads the league at 190 points with a 37-point cushion over Margaret — and Kimi Antonelli's 150-point season haul is the single biggest reason the gap looks that comfortable. Cecelia (113) and Alyssa (105) hold third and fourth, with Cecelia's remarkably steady 42-37-34 scoring run making her the most consistent manager in the league. Down at the foot of the table, Charlie (6 pts) and Jay (24 pts) are running out of races to dig themselves out.", players: { "Alyssa": "Fourth place with 105 points, and your season basically lives in Max Verstappen's AUS 50-pointer — he's scored just 14 and 13 since, which tells the story. Perez is a steady secondary contributor but won't be the one to push you into podium contention.", "Nora": "Sixth overall with 50 points, but that 47-point JPN performance is the best single-race score of the weekend and changes the vibe heading forward. Piastri's two early DNFs buried you before you started — if Japan is his floor now rather than his ceiling, a real comeback is possible.", "Jay": "Tenth with 24 points, and Valtteri Bottas is the anchor dragging you under — minus 11 for the season with DNF penalties in two of three races wiping out everything positive. Norris has 35 pts on his own and deserves a better partner.", "Margaret": "Second overall at 153 points, and George Russell's 111-point season with zero negative scores is as dependable as this league gets. Ocon has quietly added 42 more, making yours the most balanced two-driver lineup in the field.", "Cecelia": "Third place at 113 points and your consistency score is the envy of the league — three scores between 34 and 42 is just calm, professional fantasy management. Leclerc (111 pts) is the engine, but Bortoleto's CHN DNF cost you a real crack at second place.", "Timo": "League leader at 190 points and it genuinely isn't close — Kimi Antonelli's 150-point haul is the best individual driver performance in the entire competition. Bearman's JPN DNF was the only real blemish on the season, and you're still sitting 37 clear of second.", "Mary Beth": "Ninth with 38 points, and Lewis Hamilton is doing everything he can with 92 points on his own — but Lance Stroll's -54 seasonal total is an absolute catastrophe. Three straight negative races from Stroll with DNF penalties in all three means this team is being held hostage by one roster spot.", "Jane": "Fifth place at 66 points and Liam Lawson (50 pts) is firmly the carry — his CHN 35-pointer was your best single-driver score of the season. Hadjar flashed promise but a DNF in AUS and fading JPN output means he hasn't consistently had Lawson's back yet.", "David": "Eighth with 41 points, and the pattern is wearing thin — Sainz provides decent mid-table scores while Albon has broken exactly even across the season (0 pts total). JPN's combined 3-point weekend is a new low, and the trajectory isn't encouraging.", "Charlie": "Dead last with 6 points, and Fernando Alonso's -17 seasonal total is the main culprit — two DNFs in the opening two races created a hole too deep to climb out of. Lindblad has been your better driver at 23 points but fading to just 1 in JPN means neither option is inspiring right now.", "Sarah": "Seventh at 42 points, but back-to-back positive weekends in CHN and JPN suggest this team is quietly finding its feet. Gasly (45 pts) is a reliable backbone, and Hulkenberg is finally contributing after that brutal AUS DNF — the trend is the right way." } };
